>> source: https://www.traderjoes.com/home/recipes/fall-turkey-chili-with-pumpkin
>> serves: 6

In a #large saucepan{} or stockpot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add onions and @bell peppers{1} and sauté until @onions{1/2%medium} are translucent and fragrant, about 3 to ~{4%minutes}. Add @garlic{2%cloves} and stir for ~{30%seconds}. Add soy crumbles and break up in pan with #spoon, sautéing until @soy crumbles{1%pkg} is browned and cooked through. Stir in @diced tomatoes{1%can}, @pumpkin{2%cans}, @kidney beans{1%can}, @corn{1/2%can} and spices. Bring to a boil, and then reduce heat and simmer 20 to ~{30%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Garnish with @sour cream{1%cup}, @cheese{1/2%cup}, @avocado{1} and @cilantro{1%pkg}, and serve.
